The paper deals with physical layer keyless security in wireless communication, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT). The use of UAVs for jamming and optimizing the flight path involves networked systems (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also addresses the issue of eavesdropping, which is a common security concern in cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the optimization of the UAV's flight path and jamming power involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
